# Roseland-Splash — environment checklist
#
# 1) Local development (run BOTH):
#    • npm run dev        → Vite on http://localhost:8080 (proxies /api → 127.0.0.1:3001)
#    • npm run dev:api    → Express API on http://127.0.0.1:3001
#
# 2) Primary secrets live in server/.env (copy from server/.env.example).
#    Vite loads server/.env first (see vite.config.ts), so the browser Supabase client
#    and the API use the same SUPABASE_URL / anon key when configured there.
#
# 3) API must have SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY for: user_profiles upsert, Paystack order
#    updates, and admin-style routes. Without it, signup profiles and marking orders
#    paid can fail silently or error.
#
# 4) Production (e.g. Vercel):
#    • Set the same variables as in server/.env.example on the project.
#    • FRONTEND_URL = exact public site origin (Paystack callback is FRONTEND_URL/payment/verify).
#    • PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY for live or test.
#    • Prefer leaving VITE_API_URL unset so the app uses same-origin /api.
#
# Optional frontend-only overrides (uncomment if needed):
# VITE_EMAILJS_SERVICE_ID=
# VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID=
# VITE_EMAILJS_TEMPLATE_ID_CUSTOMER=
# VITE_EMAILJS_PUBLIC_KEY=
# VITE_ORDER_EMAIL=
# VITE_API_URL=
